Description: Fragment from body of transport amphora; cream slip and vertical and a horizontal reddish band on outside. Very coarse muddy reddish clay with many white inclusions; between Munsell 5YR 7/6 and 5YR 6/6 (reddish yellow); little fine dark mica; surface on inside lost completely.
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 326)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.115, p.225, pl.67)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
